cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the application of recurrent neural networks in a sequential autoencoder framework to analyze spiking neural data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses hyperparameter optimization and regularization, which are common topics in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of recurrent neural networks and autoencoders also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as possible categories. Finally, the application of these techniques to motor cortex data suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a potential category.
